Following the steps of Dijkstra's Algorithm:

Step 0 - Initialize a table or list containing distances from the starting node (3279) to every other node in the graph. Since we don't know any path yet, initialize all nodes with infinity distance except for the start node itself which will have a distance of zero. Create an empty set S to keep track of visited nodes.

