Step 3 - Choose a new node with the lowest unvisited distance (choose from neighbors and nodes without a predecessor) to be the current node; this is now the neighboring node [3165]. Mark it as visited. The table looks like: {..., 3165: 1, ...}

Step 4 - Look at all non-visited neighbors of the new current node (3165) and update their distances if needed. However, this doesn't apply here since [3279] is already visited and no other neighbor has a lower distance than infinity.

