Step 5 - Find the shortest path from starting to end by backtracking. Start from the destination node (3211), which has a direct edge [3279-3138] and another neighbor with distance 1 ([3165]) connecting through an intermediary node with distance 1 ([3138]). Hence, there are two paths:
